  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nAccording to the Ethereum API specification, `transactions` field in block object is mandatory. However, it seems that Erigon does not have the field when returning an uncle block object.\r\n(Specification link: https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis)\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nErigon version: 2022.07.4-alpha-d88fc824\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04.4 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nErigon should return a block object of the following form:\r\n<pre>\r\n{\r\n  ...\r\n  timestamp: 1659702502,\r\n  totalDifficulty: '37030977',\r\n  transactions: [],\r\n  transactionsRoot: '0x40d6b6bd0d7dfd3b17e88badf51a075ff5196271d10a892acacfefeef549cf5a',\r\n  uncles: []\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nErigon returns a block object without `transactions` field:\r\n<pre>\r\n{\r\n  ...\r\n  timestamp: 1659702502,\r\n  totalDifficulty: '37030977',\r\n  transactionsRoot: '0x40d6b6bd0d7dfd3b17e88badf51a075ff5196271d10a892acacfefeef549cf5a',\r\n  uncles: []\r\n}\r\n</pre>",
