    "body": "hi, @enriavil1 , I got here because some unrelated method of Otterscan access this internal function, and tracking it down I found the git commit.\r\n\r\nIn particular, calling `RPCMarshallBlock` with inclTx, fullTx == false, leads to the following json snipet:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"transactions\": [\r\n        null\r\n      ],\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis is because the following line assumes initial size 1:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfields[\"transactions\"] = make([]interface{}, 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think it should be `make([]interface{}, 0)`.\r\n",
